Description: Fragment of of oval handle from neck join to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine red-brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Name Philodamos. Probably same as Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 80, 20. Pencilled '98' or '86'. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0245.32.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0881)
